standards of primary enclosures , etc. 
( $number ) a primary enclosure shall be - 
(a) structurally sound and maintained in good repair ; 
(c) so constructed and maintained as to enable the animals or birds kept therein to - 
(i) remain dry and clean ; 
(ii) have convenient access to food and water ; and 
( iii ) move about freely and to stand , sit , lie and perch comfortably ; and 
(d) so located as to avoid excessive illumination . 
( $number ) housing facilities shall - 
(a) be structurally sound and maintained in good repair ; 
(d) provide sufficient space for the storage of fresh food and bedding ; 
(h) contain interior surfaces which are substantially impervious to moisture and may be readily sanitized . 
( $number ) an outdoor area shall provide - 
(c) suitable drainage for the escape of excess water . 
prohibition of alterations after grant of licence 
husbandry and sanitation 
a licensed animal trader shall comply with the following requirements - 
(a) the housing facilities , primary enclosure and outdoor area shall be maintained in a clean and sanitary condition ; 
(e) the water supplied to the animals or birds shall be potable and uncontaminated ; 
(f) food and water receptacles shall be - 
(i) readily accessible to animals and birds ; 
(ii) kept clean ; and 
(g) a supply of disinfectants shall be available for purposes of sanitation . 
certain animals or birds to be kept separate 
( $number ) notwithstanding that they are of the same , or of a compatible , genus - 
(b) animals or birds of vicious disposition shall be housed individually in separate primary enclosures ; 
(d) animals or birds under treatment for a communicable disease shall be kept separate from other animals or birds . 
prohibition on hawking 
no person shall hawk an animal or bird . 
unweaned animals not to be sold 
no person shall sell an unweaned animal . 
