chilling and defrosting tanks 
chilling and defrosting tanks shall be - 
(a) made of metal or other suitable material which is impervious to moisture ; 
(b) of seamless construction , with the edges rolled outwards ; and 
(c) of such a size that a person may empty the tanks without having to climb inside them . 
