liability for nuisance not affected 
nothing in these regulations or in a licence granted under them shall - 
(a) authorize the commission of a nuisance ; 
(b) affect the liability of any person in respect of a nuisance ; or 
(c) restrict or remove the right or power of any person to abate a nuisance . 
manner of signifying approval of director 
the director shall signify any approval , authorization or consent given by him under these regulations either - 
(a) generally , by notice in the gazette , or 
(b) in any particular case , in writing . 
offences 
commencement of prosecutions 
prosecutions for offences under these regulations shall not be commenced without the consent in writing of the director . 
power of director to give directions to licensee 
the director may give the licensee such directions as he thinks fit for the purposes of these regulations . 
