empowering section 
[ $number june $number ] 
citation 
these regulations may be cited as the public health ( animals and birds ) ( exhibitions ) regulations . 
interpretation 
( $number ) in these regulations unless the context otherwise requires - 
prohibition of exhibiting animals or birds without licence or permit 
power of director to grant licence 
( $number ) a licence shall not be granted or renewed unless - 
(a) the director has inspected and approved the place at which the exhibition is to be held ; and 
( $number ) the director may attach to a licence such conditions as he may think fit . 
( $number ) a licence shall specify - 
(a) the residential address of the person licensed to hold the exhibition ; 
(b) the address of the place at which the exhibition may be held ; and 
(c) the place at which the animals or birds for the purpose of exhibition may be kept . 
standards of primary enclosures etc. 
( $number ) a primary enclosure shall be - 
(a) structurally sound and maintained in good repair ; 
(c) constructed and maintained so as to enable the animals or birds contained therein to - 
(i) remain dry and clean ; 
(ii) have convenient access to food and water ; and 
( iii ) move about freely and to stand , sit , lie and perch comfortably ; and 
(d) located so as to avoid excessive illumination . 
( $number ) housing facilities shall - 
(a) be structurally sound and maintained in good repair ; 
(c) contain an adequate supply of potable water and suitable drainage for the escape of excess water ; 
(d) provide sufficient space for the storage of fresh food and bedding ; 
(h) contain interior surfaces which are substantially impervious to moisture and may be sanitarily cleaned at all times . 
( $number ) an outdoor area shall provide - 
(a) sufficient shade to enable the animals or birds to protect themselves from the direct rays of the sun ; 
(b) adequate shelter to allow the animals or birds protection in inclement weather ; 
(c) suitable drainage for the escape of excess water . 
except with the prior consent of the director , no person to whom a licence has been granted shall - 
husbandry and sanitation 
(b) all food and water receptacles for the animals or birds shall be - 
(i) readily accessible to the animals or birds ; 
(ii) so located as to minimize contamination by excreta or otherwise ; 
(iv) kept in good condition at all times ; 
(e) the primary enclosures , housing facilities and outdoor areas shall be maintained in a sanitary condition ; 
(h) notwithstanding that the animals or birds are of the same or a compatible genus - 
(ii) they shall be housed individually in separate primary enclosures if they are of vicious disposition . 
power of director to grant permit 
( $number ) the director may attach to a permit such conditions as he may think fit . 
( $number ) a permit shall specify - 
(a) the particulars of the person to whom the permit is issued ; 
(b) the place at which the exhibition may be held ; and 
(c) the place at which the animals or birds for the purpose of exhibition may be kept . 
offences and penalties 
( $number ) any person to whom a licence has been granted who contravenes - 
(a) any condition attached to his licence ; or 
(b) regulation $number or $number , 
shall be guilty of an offence and shall be liable on conviction to a fine of $ $number . 
