(b) the address of the place at which the boarding establishment for animals may be kept . 
standards of primary enclosures etc. 
( $number ) a primary enclosure shall be - 
(a) structurally sound and maintained in good repair ; 
(c) constructed and maintained so as to enable the animals accommodated therein to - 
(i) remain dry and clean ; 
(ii) have convenient access to food and water ; and 
( iii ) move about freely and to stand , sit or lie comfortably ; and 
(d) located so as to avoid excessive illumination . 
( $number ) housing facilities shall - 
(a) be structurally sound and maintained in good repair ; 
(b) be designed so as to contain the animals accommodated therein and to restrict the entrance of other animals ; 
(d) provide sufficient space for the storage of fresh food and bedding ; 
(h) contain interior surfaces which are substantially impervious to moisture and may be sanitarily cleaned at all times . 
( $number ) an outdoor area shall provide - 
(a) sufficient shade to enable the animals to protect themselves from the direct rays of the sun ; 
(b) adequate shelter to allow the animals protection in inclement weather ; and 
(c) suitable drainage for the escape of excess water . 
except with the prior consent of the director , no person to whom a licence has been granted shall - 
husbandry and sanitation 
(b) all food and water receptacles for the animals shall be - 
(i) readily accessible to the animals ; 
(ii) so located as to minimize contamination by excreta or otherwise ; 
(iv) kept in good condition at all times ; 
(h) notwithstanding that the animals are of the same or compatible genus - 
(ii) animals of vicious disposition shall be housed individually in separate primary enclosures ; 
(i) when permanently maintained in breeding colonies ; or 
(ii) where the adult animals are their dams or equivalent ; 
(j) dogs and cats shall not be housed in the same primary enclosure ; 
(k) dogs or cats shall not be housed with any other species of animals ; and 
(l) animals under treatment for a communicable disease shall be kept separate from other animals . 
