interpretation 
in these rules , unless the context otherwise requires - 
obligation to pay into client account 
payment into client account 
there may be paid into a client account - 
(a) trust money ; 
splitting 
restriction on payment into client account 
drawings from a client account 
there may be drawn from a client account - 
(a) in the case of client 's money - 
(i) money properly required for a payment to or on behalf of the client ; 
( iii ) money drawn on the client 's authority ; and 
(b) in the case of trust money , including money held by the solicitor as solicitor - trustee - 
(i) money properly required for a payment in the execution of the particular trust ; and 
further restrictions on drawings from client account 
(a) a cheque drawn in favour of the solicitor ; or 
(b) a transfer to a bank account in the name of the solicitor not being a client account . 
exceptions 
(a) the client for his own convenience requests the solicitor to withhold from such account ; or 
